annotationA: 60S ribosomal protein L7a; Structural constituent of ribosome. It is involved in the biological process described with: ribosome biogenesis; mitotic spindle elongation; centrosome organization; translation; centrosome duplication; mitotic spindle organization; Belongs to the eukaryotic ribosomal protein eL8 family
annotationB: Probable ribosome biogenesis protein RLP24; Involved in the biogenesis of the 60S ribosomal subunit. Ensures the docking of NOG1 to pre-60S particles (By similarity)
